<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
    <title>WEIGHT LOSS</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="Case_sheet_styles.css">
    <link id="dark-styles" rel="alternate stylesheet" title="dark" href="Case_sheet_styles_dark.css">
    <script src="https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode">🌙 Dark Mode</button>
    
    <h4>Weight Loss</h4>
    <div class="General">
        <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: WEIGHT LOSS</h3>
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Site (of perceived loss)</span>
                <span class="verbal">"Where have you noticed the weight loss the most? For example, in your face, or do your clothes feel looser around your waist?"</span>
                <ul>
                    <li class="General">Generalised loss of fat and/or muscle</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>: Onset</span>
                <span class="verbal">"When did you or others first notice you were losing weight?"</span>
                <ul>
                    <li class="oncology infectious endocrine">Rapid (over weeks)</li>
                    <li class="General oncology psychiatric">Gradual (over months)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>: Duration</span>
                <span class="verbal">"For how long has this been happening?"</span>
            </li>
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>: Aggravating & Relieving Factors</span>
                <span class="verbal">"Have you made any changes to your diet or exercise? Has anything seemed to slow or speed up the weight loss?"</span>
            </li>
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>: Character & Quantification</span>
                <span class="verbal">"First, was this weight loss intentional? How much weight have you lost, and over what period? And how has your appetite been?"</span>
                <ul>
                    <li class="General">INTENTIONAL vs. UNINTENTIONAL (Crucial first question)</li>
                    <li class="General">AMOUNT: Quantify in kg or lbs; percentage of body weight (>5% in 6 months is significant)</li>
                    <li class="">APPETITE (Key Differentiator)
                        <ul>
                            <li class="endocrine git">INCREASED APPETITE (or normal)
                                <ul>
                                    <li class="endocrine">Hyperthyroidism</li>
                                    <li class="endocrine">Poorly controlled Diabetes Mellitus</li>
                                    <li class="git">Malabsorption (e.g., Celiac disease, pancreatic insufficiency)</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li class="oncology psychiatric infectious">DECREASED APPETITE (Anorexia)
                                <ul>
                                    <li class="oncology">Malignancy</li>
                                    <li class="psychiatric">Depression / Anxiety</li>
                                    <li class="infectious">Chronic infection (e.g., TB, HIV)</li>
                                    <li class="cvs nephro respiratory">Chronic disease (cardiac, renal, respiratory failure)</li>
                                    <li class="git">GI disorders (PUD, gastritis, IBD)</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Radiation</span>
                <span class="verbal">"Not applicable for this complaint."</span>
            </li>
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>: Associated Symptoms</span>
                <span class="verbal">"Along with the weight loss, have you experienced any other symptoms like fever, pain, or changes in your habits?"</span>
                <ul>
                    <li class="oncology infectious">CONSTITUTIONAL
                        <ul>
                            <li class="oncology infectious hematology">Fever, night sweats, fatigue (malaise)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li class="git oncology">GASTROINTESTINAL
                        <ul>
                            <li class="git oncology">Change in bowel habit (diarrhea, constipation)</li>
                            <li class="git">Diarrhea, steatorrhea (pale, floating, foul-smelling stools)</li>
                            <li class="git oncology">Difficulty or pain swallowing (dysphagia, odynophagia)</li>
                            <li class="git">Abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, early satiety</li>
                            <li class="git hematology oncology">Rectal bleeding or melena (black stools)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li class="endocrine">ENDOCRINE
                        <ul>
                            <li class="endocrine cvs psychiatric">Heat intolerance, palpitations, anxiety, tremor, diarrhea (Hyperthyroidism)</li>
                            <li class="endocrine nephro">Excessive thirst (polydipsia), excessive urination (polyuria) (Diabetes)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li class="respiratory oncology infectious">RESPIRATORY
                        <ul>
                            <li class="respiratory">Chronic cough</li>
                            <li class="respiratory oncology hematology">Coughing up blood (hemoptysis)</li>
                            <li class="respiratory cvs">Shortness of breath</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                     <li class="psychiatric">PSYCHIATRIC
                        <ul>
                            <li class="psychiatric">Low mood, loss of interest/pleasure (anhedonia)</li>
                            <li class="psychiatric">Sleep disturbance, anxiety, altered body image</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li class="cns oncology">NEUROLOGICAL
                        <ul>
                            <li class="cns">Muscle weakness, fasciculations</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Progression</span>
                <span class="verbal">"Is the weight loss continuing, or has it levelled off? Is it happening faster now?"</span>
            </li>
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Pattern</span>
                <span class="verbal">"Is the weight loss continuous, or does it fluctuate?"</span>
            </li>
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>: Effect on Life</span>
                <span class="verbal">"How has this weight loss affected you? Have you noticed your clothes are looser or that you feel weaker?"</span>
                <ul>
                    <li class="General">Functional decline, weakness</li>
                    <li class="General">Comments from friends/family</li>
                    <li class="psychiatric">Psychological distress</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Red Flags</span>
                <span class="verbal">"I just need to ask some specific questions to be thorough."</span>
                <ul>
                    <li class="oncology git">DIFFICULTY SWALLOWING (Dysphagia)</li>
                    <li class="oncology infectious hematology">PERSISTENT FEVER or DRENCHING NIGHT SWEATS</li>
                    <li class="oncology hematology git respiratory nephro">ANY UNEXPLAINED BLEEDING (from any site)</li>
                    <li class="oncology">NEW PALPABLE LUMP</li>
                    <li class="oncology git">RECENT, PERSISTENT CHANGE in BOWEL HABIT (especially > 40-50 yrs)</li>
                    <li class="oncology respiratory hematology">COUGHING UP BLOOD (Hemoptysis)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="point">
                <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Severity / Scale</span>
                <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10, how concerned are you about this weight loss?"</span>
            </li>
    </div>
    
    <script src="theme-toggle.js"></script>
    <script src="Iframe_height_mothership.js"></script>
    <script src="Iframe_height.js"></script>
  <script src="double_click_collapse_details.js"></script>
  


  </body>
</html>
